    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-06-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-06-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="510"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d510">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Sir <persName
                            type="to">M. H. Herbert</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-06-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 22, 1903</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: I have your letter of the 18th
                    of June, acknowledging receipt of mine of the 16th, and calling attention to
                    certain points in which our recollections of conversations seem not exactly to
                    agree. I take note of your corrections, which do not seem in any essential point
                    to affect the action of the two Governments in the case, and am, my dear Sir
                    Michael,</p>
                <p>Very sincerely, yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
